Czech discovery: a substance, which is also in 'like' HIV viruses works
The team of Czech and German scientists testing new compounds designed to prevent the spread of HIV virus in the body.
The main advantage of improved substance is that he is also in the viruses, which are resistant to drugs.
This fact outweighs against the disadvantage that the link to normal virus-variants not as strong as one of the existing medicines.
The disease AIDS cannot be cured.
The patients, the medication compilation but can prolong the lives and prevent the proliferation of the HIV virus in the body.
Their use is accompanied by a whole series of side effects.
Incomplete oppression of the viral reproduction also has the development sg. Resistent viruses result against no medicines are more effective.
The work of the experts from the three institutions of the Academy of Sciences CR, from the VSCHT (chemically-Technological High School) Prague, from the University of Heidelberg opens the way of how to deal with the virus-resistant.
They have proven that as Metalokarborane substances on the protein substance, which is responsible for the expansion of HIV Viruses.
The Metalokarborane are links from Bor, hydrogen, carbon and cobalt.
These compounds block the virus reproduction in other ways than all drugs used today, so they can overcome the resistance problem.
In their work, the scientists to new ´ improved ´ links, on the basis of knowledge of the molecular mechanism of their attachment to the virus protein material were prepared.
The Metalokarborane have a unique three-dimensional structure: two vielfächige cages from Bor -, hydrogen and carbon atoms, and through a metal atom, in this case, cobalt, are linked.
Heinous and constant virus
HIV Protease is protein material of the HIV virus, which for the life cycle of the virus is essential.
Without the HIV Protease caused by the HIV virus division would not Infektionsvirenpartikel mature.
If we eliminate the HIV Protease, we call the propagation of the virus in the body of the patients from, say the scientists in the press report, by the Institute for organic chemistry and biochemistry of the Academy of Sciences CR.
In the work in the Science paper Journal of Medicinal Chemistry was published, the scientists describe all ranks of the compounds, in which two couples the cages (see table) by a brief organic chain are linked, then further changed systematically.
A weaker, but reliable
The impact of this series of substances against the HIV-Protease wurdne tested in Reagenzglas, even against their steady (resistant) variations which were won by HIV-infected patients.
The impact of the Metalokarborane in the usual enzyme variant is not as strong as the clinically used medicines, but they do not lose their effect on the Resistentvarianten, against which the medicines are often ineffective.
The unique impact mechanism and its other properties, such as the biological and chemical stability, low toxicity and the possibility of further chemical ways, makes the Metalokarboranen to interesting links for further on the development of effective medicines against HIV applied research, says Pavlina Rezacova, head of the laboratory for structural biology of the Institute for organic chemistry and biochemistry and the Institute for molecular genetics of the Academy of Sciences.
