After the new road map of the CD (Czech railways) will drive less trains for roughly the same fare.
The Czech Railways stopped or restricted from 13 December some less closing its rapid and local trains, other links will be strengthened.
The entire transport volume will be reduced from the day of the new road map compared with today at two percent.
Most tariffs incl. Basic and Kundenfahrtarif will not be changed.
Several liaison possibilities in the capital, for example, the residents of Ostrava area, the railways for this line trains of the type Pendolino.
The train will no longer be Bratislava (former Pressburg).
Less fast trains are also on the route Prague - Pisek - drive Budweis, in principle, the direct links from Prague to Letohrad.
The biggest reduction in the railways in the district of Hradec Kralove (King Graz), an of eight percent, to an increase in Prague and environment.
Be lifted two night trains on the route Prague - Tabor - Budweis and on some days in the week of the operation of some fast trains on the route Prague - Pisek - reduced Budweis.
The biggest changes include the introduction of the new Direktverkehrsweges from Milovice to Prague, at the moment, the inhabitants of Milovice in Lysa nad Labem.
It is the fifteenth route of suburban transport system Esko, whose opening thanks to the railway electrification from Lysa nad Labem after Milovice is possible.
The long-distance routes in the capital will end in the target station Prague - main railway station.
The CD introduces more lines sc pendolino between Prague and Ostrava and the trains after sumperk / jesenik in the space of two hours.
With the Pendolino the passengers since 13 December can no longer go to Bratislava.
