We already have all our time and energy in a child.
For a second child is nothing left, said Wang, 31, a staff leader with an 8-month old son.
More than 30 years after the introduction of the one-child policy in China, the two generations of notoriously dicklichen, spoiled individual children, who affectionately called "little emperors", has produced a population crisis in the country.
The average birth rate is at 1.8 children per couple, compared to 6 at the time, as this policy came into force, the UN is.
Department for population issues, while the number of population of 60 years and older in 2020 from 16.7 percent of the population by the year 2050 to 31.1 percent rise exponentially. This is well above the global average of around 20 percent.
The imbalance is in rich coastal cities with educated population, such as Shanghai, stronger.
Last year have 60-jährige and older almost 22 percent of reported residents identified Shanghai, while the birth rate of one child per couple.
Xie Lingli, head of the Shanghai city population and family planning Commission has said that couples should receive normal reproductive age babies, "in order to help to reduce the relationship of the ageing population and to alleviate the labour shortage in the future ".
Shanghai will soon "as old -- but not as rich as the industrialised countries, such as Japan and Sweden," she said.
A gradual relaxation
enshrined in the constitution of the country in 1978, China's one-child policy would be the most controversial disposal, which was introduced by the ruling Communist Party until today.
Couples who are against this policy, must reckon with huge fines -- triple up on her annual salary in some regions -- and with discrimination in the workplace.
Chinese state representatives have attributed this policy that the critical financial pressure on the natural land resources could be avoided, while human rights activists have condemned abuses in the enforcement of the policy.
In rural areas, some officials pregnant women who have already had a child, forced to Abzutreiben.
Many couples have had geschlechtsselektive abortions, and take an unnatural high ratio of men to women.
In recent years, government representatives for population gradually their position on the one-child policy weakened.
In 2004, they have allowed more exceptions to the rule -- including urban dwellers and members of ethnic minorities and cases in which both husband and wife have been Einzelkinder -- and 2007 was moderated by the tone of many hard slogans.
Qiao Xiaochun, a professor at the Institute for Population Research at the University of Beijing said that government officials recently discussed even more radical changes, for example, couples to allow two children, in which a Einzelkind partner.
