Martin Poole, 50, a television marketing assistant from Hove, is a voluntary cleric of the Chichester-situation and director of Beyond.
He said: "We want religion for the people in a post-christlichen society more important.
Why do we as the church of the people that they are in a strange old building, I think the church should go to the people and enthusiastic celebration.
The idea for the beach huts-advent calendar, began as a conversation with some friends at dinner.
Brighton is such a fantastic creative and lively place and we try to express this through our spirituality. "
Late payment: angry prison guards, actions planned
The unions of prison officials have called on Friday to a general day of action to ensure that the bonuses and overtime, whose pay for budget reasons was postponed until January, before the Christmas holidays.
The 2nd union of prison officials ("FO-Pénitentiaire"), urged the staff who have no service to demonstrate on Tuesday morning before the detention center and to block this order to the "theft of what they are entitled" to draw attention.
The third union of prison officials ("CGT-Pénitentiaire") called on to unite "to a strong mobilisation in various prisons," in which the non-payment of overtime incurred in October, night increments and Sundays and holiday surcharges in December as "disgraceful and unacceptable" distilled market.
The first trade union of prison officials, the autonomous federal Strafanstaltsunion (UFAP / UNSA), called for "general mobilisations (…) to show the discontent and anger."
The management of the prison and the Ministry of Justice said that the overtime in 2009 have increased sharply and were not in the budget. they guarantee, however, that the remaining claims will be paid in January.
As the Justice Department in the evening, Michèle Alliot-Marie is the unions of prison officials sent a letter in which ensures that the payment next month.
"I am very aware of the efforts of the staff, our prison system to function and to modernise," shares the minister of justice in this letter.
"I have the leadership of the prison clinic to take immediate measures to ensure that such a situation caused by a lack of assessment of overtime is not repeated in the future," added Mrs Alliot-Marie.
The December wage is therefore little, except for the management staff, who enjoy high pay and bonuses, said the UFAP / UNSA, for which the "budgetary constraints" must be used.
"this is an absolute scandal" outraged the interregional trade union FO in Marseille and announces, "all the meetings and notices of meetings" to the new instructions to boycott.
"The staff is not on Sundays and public holidays to work, if the hours of October in December have still not been paid. This also applies to their overtime," there is also the FO Rhône-Alpes-Auvergne.
"at a time when more and more tasks, without more staff, is the attempt to enrich themselves of the money of staff, more than inappropriate," the CGT union of Bordeaux.
According to the trade unions, the situation is not the same in all regions. Some are less affected than others.
In any case, however, it is wrong, according to the Secretary-General of the UFAP, Jean-Francois Forget.
