Managers revolution or the end of the Strategic early education?
If nothing will change in the leadership of the major French companies, our fight for the development of the economic intelligence in vain...
For over a decade, the attitude of the management of large companies in relation to his staff, said the position of the company vis à vis consumers from the marketing revolution: it is to join the staff "values" determines the best, as it was made at the consumer products from the technicians in the station to impose.
By customers in the heart of the company has the marketing revolution the strategies of the conquest of the markets in the ground... Although separated the authoritarian temptation products separately factors preferences of customers to impose regularly again!
A demobilisation of staff can lead to a deadly demoralisation.
The suicides at France Telecom, PSA and Renault are only the tip of a much larger phenomenon, in particular the employees affected.
This demobilization has a negative impact on the development of all intellectual functions of the company, in particular those of R & eund, even more importantly, to those of the economic intelligence.
In fact, calls on the IE (Intelligence Economique = economic intelligence) "from all parties involved (...) a proactive approach and a forward-looking Sichtweise";sie claims by the staff of a deployment, which the instructions of the authoritarian management completely contradictory.
That is why we are calling for an occupational revolution, which would be the staff at the heart of the concerns of the company equal to the customers.
The very conditional use of internal polls
The internal polls, as the questionnaire, the Orange has submitted his wage workers, this revolution in relation to the management practice?
I fear that, unfortunately not.
- firstly, because I could see that the entire structure with a new situation after many Roundabout is concerned, priority... to do what it has always done.
Also because of the authoritarianism - one of the pathologies of power in proportion to the importance of his own failures.
And finally, because most leaders have a much simplified idea of human behaviour.
emerged from the great engineering schools is their interpretation of the psychology mechanistic.
They play by intellectual comfort the old behavioristische theory, which recently by the U.S. American "neuroscience" reactivated and unknowingly far-reaching research institutes and through the media.
Thus, and it suggests that it is possible to work the "leverage" (sic) on the involvement of employees, reinforced a aktuellein Le appeared Figaro.fr poll by Ipsos executives in a position to a mechanistic control system, which is unsuitable for today's world.
The mobilisation factors identify and measure
Instead, a for the smooth functioning of the modern companies necessary occupational revolution the adoption of a final view of human behavior.
It is, in any consideration or practice of management to integrate a fundamental record: for the wage-earners is the commitment to the company will only be possible if it clearly appears as a means to achieve a portion of their dreams, their ambition and their projects.
Now take only the studies from the multifunctional analysis of this concept of the motivation of the staff.
These studies have shown that they allowed their companies on the basis of a specified Doxa judge them by their perceived image of the company, to assess what it offers them to achieve their life goals.
Thanks to the identification and the measurement of these factors can mobilise the executives of the companies' social services ", to predict and anticipate and invest its human resource management back to the right place.
So they create a fertile ground for the coordinated development of a robust and efficient economic intelligence is favourable.
