Dream worlds
Some people see in wachem state images and hear voices, others do not see or hear.
Not only in mental health and drug binge blurs the boundaries between imagination and reality.
As long as it happens in their sleep, everything is in order.
If we are with closed eyes in our dark rooms, we must likes the wildest ideas and Phantasiegebilden.
Anyone who witnessed in a guard traumartige conditions, things can see and hear, see the others do not or hear applies in the modern Western world mostly as crazy or drug addicts, at least as a Sonderling.
But such images and voices arise not only in mental health or drug binge.
Blame our imagination: the same neural processes that enable us to design houses, paint pictures or to write novels, sometimes to ensure that the boundaries between dream, cow and reality.
Traumartig modified Wachbewusstseinszustände can occur in different forms, in the best case we call them visions, in the worst case madness.
Even if the trigger and effect may distinguish the visions of the Mystikerin Hildegard of Bingen, the drug experiences of New-Age-prophet Carlos Castaneda, schamanische Entrückungszustände, psychosis and hallucinations but similar processes.
Hallucinations or delusions, if the balance of the neural messenger substances of the brain - Dopamin, noradrenaline, serotonin and Acetylcholin - and the interaction of various parts of the brain is disrupted.
Complex hallucinations and wahnhafte thoughts are very often during a schizophrenic psychosis.
The gravity has no power over him
The context of madness and dream, philosophers and doctors since ancient times.
Aristotle understood hallucinations as a form of the dream in the eye condition, Wilhelm Griesinger, one of the founders of the modern psychiatry, 1861 noted a "great similarity of mistaken one with a dream conditions" for Sigmund Freud was the dream even "a climate, with all the inconsistency, Wahnbildungen, meaning deceit of such".
It is the autumn of 2001, when Henning T. in a comic figure.
His body is two dimensions and quietschbunt.
The gravity has no power more about him, he is hanging in the bedroom ceiling.
He senses a kick.
Behind him runs devil figures with blutroten, distorted Fratzen, zähnefletschend.
They chase him, him with serious, inflammatory boots, throwing him against the walls, he feels the pain in the whole body.
Noisy, malicious voices roar from walls and radio.
He can no longer bear the votes to attack and insult him.
Henning T. snaps two cable from the stereo, knotet to a noose and consolidating them in a hole in the ceiling.
It is rising on a loudspeaker and establishes the noose around the neck.
Jumping one.
The noose resolves itself.
This should be a lesson to you, the voices in trommelfellzerfetzendem choir, "Walk in the clinic and let you cure!"
Today, Henning T. is 40 years old, he has seen six acute psychosis, the last is 2 years ago, the first of nearly 20 years.
It was triggered by LSD.
His diagnosis is schizoaffektive-paranoid psychosis, moreover, he is bi-low, he takes medicines against depression, mania, the schizophrenia.
He has learned to live with his disease, for three years, he is married.
In the climate of I have seen worst fear and deepest despair, he says.
The images are cruel reality
About one percent of the population contracted at least once a life with schizophrenia, in psychiatric clinics it is treated as the second most common illness after the depression.
In an acute psychosis schizophrenic affected mostly can no longer distinguish between the internal and external world, they get trapped in a übererregten state of hallucinations, scale, relationships or paranoia can lead.
It is particularly prevalent stimmenhören - voices orders, comment on or dialogisieren.
Also optical hallucinations are not rare.
The person concerned is important to distinguish between what is trivial, the brain can no longer ausfiltern disturbing signals, the awareness is being inundated with impressions.
As the dream also opens the psychosis the floodgates for a flood of ideas and fantasies, the deeper awareness classes.
The reality of perception in the climate is subjektzentriert, says Professor Thomas fox, Oberarzt the clinic for General Psychiatry in the Universitätsklinikum Heidelberg.
The schizophrenic is in the heart of the storm, everything has its importance to him.
At the same time, he is in a passive role, he will, as happens in the dream, of the events overwhelmed and can you not actively shape.
Schizophrenic often feel threatened, controlled and manipulated.
A Realitätsabgleich is usually not possible, the Mere empty are cruel reality, wake up.
Once in a lifetime to have experienced a Halluzination
Unlike in the dream, says fox, "but the sinnliche and spatial structure of reality, which is perceived in the psychosis, basically."
The obsessive thoughts and hallucinations based in reality, the Verfremdung of the Erlebens will take place in real terms.
Why exactly our brains antics proposes, researchers are still a mystery.
Exceptional situations in every person can lead that he loses touch with the short-term, says fox.
But not everyone will develop a psychosis.
It seems to be a genetic predisposition to schizophrenia, but twin studies have shown that the genes are not the only determinants.
Researchers assume that affected minimal brain damage.
We suspect that the neuronale maturing of the brain at an early stage of development, will be disrupted by a viral infection of the mother during pregnancy, for example, explained Fox.
But it remains a mystery, as the disruption of the neural system, the manifestiere not also first over many years.
Environmental factors also play a role - stress or traumatic experiences can be a trigger for psychosis, if the overdraft is there.
Also halluzinogene drugs can trigger psychosis, since they intervene in the transmitter system.
If our brain is hot
The nutcases, Psychotiker suffer their hallucinations and swallow expensive drugs in order to get rid of them, others give money for drugs in order to get out, which, says the Lübecker psychology professor Erich castes.
Whether related images as pleasant or unpleasant, is often only a question of the position.
Caste collects for ten years, reports of hallucinations and wore phenomena, last year, he has evaluated its results in the book "The unreal world in our heads".
Hallucinations are among the typical effects of psychosis, but also of astonishing many other diseases.
These include mental disorders, such as Borderline or depression often diseases such as migraine, epilepsy, multiple sclerosis, or Alzheimer's disease and Schädelhirntraumata.
Surprisingly, hallucinates under certain conditions, even the brain healthy people.
Hallucinations, so caste, from memory content, which would normally be withheld.
They arise if brain stretches, in which sensory processed, actively discouraged or too little; if our brain is hot, or even if stimulation is missing.
Drugs can trigger this state as well as brain damage or a psychosis.
But also appeal of deprivation, stress, love grief or other mental emergency situations.
In recent studies, up to a third of those polled said that at least once in their lives to have experienced a hallucinations.
In the summer of 2005, Sarah K. 16 years old, she lives in a small town in Mecklenburg-Western Pomerania and visited the school there.
A normal girl, really.
If it not for the images and voices.
In the break, it can happen that a schlaksiger boy with long, dark hair it addresses.
If he says the classmates look surprisingly - no one else sees or hears these boys.
They think the timid girl for a stop Tagträumerin, but Sarah K. not dreaming, it knows it.
It is, they see or hear these boys, just as the girls in the bank alongside to see or hear.
You can even feel his presence, at least for moments.
A pleasant feeling is that they may be the boys.
Am I crazy?, asks them sometimes.
But she knows that this boy and the other was wearing images are not real, and then disappear again.
At night, the phenomena mostly frightening
Often the trick images are also a burden.
If you are sitting in the class room, they can follow the teaching material sometimes not because the teachers in their eyes and ears just presents a new classmates, while he explained for all other visually and visible on the table mathematical equations.
At night, the phenomena are mostly frightening.
If they wait in their dark room on sleep, which is far too little and far too late, they can often not distinguish whether she is awake or dreams, whether the pictures she sees that Fratzen or the girl arise with the bleeding wounds on average, arms and legs, above its open or closed eyes.
Let me in peace, they are the characters.
Parents and friends told them nothing, which would be crazy.
Autumn 2009. Sarah K. is now 20 years old.
She has in the past year the baccalaureate and lives with her friend.
A year ago, the hallucinations stopped.
Since the Internet contact with the psychologists caste, it knows full well that they are not crazy.
Madness is also a work of art from despair
If someone is socially isolated or under reizentzug he has, in all probability, after a while hallucinations, says castes.
I suspect that the brain is then unterbeschäftigt and even for his entertainment.
Sarah K., a Einzelkind, had as a little girl fear of other children, they often played alone.
Their hallucinations began with 13 learned that the man known as Papa, since they can think of is not their leiblicher father.
As visual and acoustic hallucinations the same brain areas are active, the real impressions and noise, it is affected as Sarah k. difficult to distinguish related images and reality-China. "every experience," says caste, "will take place in the brain, the reality is there.
Hallucinations are also images of the brain, that is why they are so real. "
Also night dream images of digesting caste as a form of hallucinations.
The hallucinations of healthy do not differ fundamentally from those of an acute psychosis.
Unlike schizophrenic are mentally healthy in the situation, their fantasy images as unreal.
Caste advises his patients, therefore, the hallucinations as a special ability wertzuschätzen.
Border state between dream and hallucinations
In our very bewusstseinszentrierten world imaginary experience, unfortunately, most pathologisiert, says Michael Schmidt Degenhard, professor in Heidelberg and chief doctor of the clinic for psychiatry and psychotherapy of Florence Nightingale Krankenhauses in Düsseldorf.
A psychosis is a heavy, painful disease, but it also has positive, creative - obsession is also a work of art out of desperation.
Schmidt rapier hardware has researched the so-called oneiroide experience form, a particular form of traumartig modified guard awareness.
Oneiroide are highly complex, detailed quasi-dreams, which holds the Erlebende for real and he also retrospectively cannot distinguish from wakefulness.
The oneiroide bewusstseinszustand arises in trauma- or illness extreme situations, for example in polyradikulitis-patienten in full awareness of a motor paralysis.
If a man of self- and world loss is threatened by continued, total impotence, it replaces the life-threatening reality through a separate, imaginary world, which is decoupled from the reality, says Schmidt-rapier going hard.
A kind of border state between dream and hallucinations.
Since the deal with a situation in reality is not possible, a world of letters, but the real situation in the Imagination.
An intensive form of good Foundation and meaning in an intolerable situation that allows us people own ability, not in a nothing of the Bewusstseinsverlustes.
Everything is real, later in the memory
Also the Zürcher art historian Peter Cornelius Claussen describes his Oneiroid-experiences in his book "heart change" as a bailout of the soul.
He is 49 years old when his consciousness after a heart valves operation, followed by a heart transplant for days on travel, while his body at the intensive care unit for Bewegungslosigkeit.
Claussen, a world in a selbstgeschaffene visited foreign times and places: he is seen as bettlägerigen, old man, on board a zugsanatoriums, a robot guard on his health.
He lives in the early Middle Ages under nobles manufacturing drugs from blood.
By a Greeks on the motorcycle in his home country, surfing with his hospital bed in Firnschnee the Alps and hits a Korean Mafioso.
He is completely in the imagined events, everything is real, later in the memory.
These internal travel for Claussen differ fundamentally from any dream.
Dream is a different state, he describes his experience.
In contrast, the memories from mental travel even after years and in secondary details abundantly clear.
More and more even than really Erlebtes.
The intensity of this Erlebens goes beyond the horizon of our other secular life experience, says the psychiatrist Schmidt-Degen hard.
Ultimately, show Oneiroide psychoses, hallucinations and drugs binge, how fragile our internal figures of external reality in the guards.
Any change in the Bewusstseinszustandes, say the psychologist caste, "can lead to a Verformung of what we call reality."
An experience which may also be enriching.
