The support for Bremsmanövern in critical situations is now duty
As it was the Antiblockierbremssystem ABS and how it is now happening with the ESP stability control ESP, must auxiliary systems on the brakes in the increase in the European cars.
In fact, they are already duty all newly registered passenger cars and light trucks, for the remaining vehicles has set a waiting period until the end of February 2011.
The decision by the European Union Manahme aims to improve the protection of the Fugänger, but these braking systems because of their operation also help to prevent many front-rear collisions.
The task of the Notbremsassistenten is more pressure on the brakes in the event of a critical Bremsmanövers, which recognises the system on the basis of the drivers Bremsstärke carried out on the brake pedal to exercise.
However, this system is not this pressure until the end.
According to one of the components manufacturer for the Bosch vehicles commissioned inquiry, a third of the drivers involved in an accident before the toss, not more to come on the brake pedal and half of them had not slowed down with full force.
Up to 1,100 accidents
The Bremshilfe against resorts with maximum force in the braking system and reduce the Bremszeit and therefore also the Bremsabstand, a car in the Bremsvorgang back.
According to a study by the EU could each year up to 1,100 fatal accidents involving pedestrians to damage, be prevented if all cars were equipped with this type of Notbremsassistenten.
It would even be less accidents - it is calculated that every fourth accident involving personal injury could be avoided - as soon as the so-called intelligent emergency braking are popular.
Then the vehicle is equipped with a system that (on radar or a camera) obstacles and warns the driver, and at the same time, a light pressure on the brakes.
If the driver then, helps him the system to increase the pressure on the brake pedal, if it would be necessary.
If the driver does not respond to the warning and even if the toss is unavoidable, the Bremsassistent the maximum pressure on the brakes from, in order to keep the damage as much as possible.
