Associated industries
The chairman of Iberdrola, Ignacio Sánchez Galán, came as the first yesterday before the subcommittee of the House, where the strategy in relation to the energy supply of Spain in the next two decades.
After his appearance, the chairman of the Gas Natural-Fenosa, Rafael Villaseca followed Galán the press gave some key points about what he had submitted to the subcommittee behind versschlossenen doors.
According to the chairman of Iberdrola Spain must 50 billion by 2020 Euround further 60 billion to invest from that date until 2030, under the promotion that the current nuclear power stations will continue to remain in operation.
Should this not be the case, would the investment needed to 60 billion, but up to 95 billion.
However, Iberdrola is of the opinion that we should not invest more in an increase in energy production capacity, but in distribution networks and international groupings.
From 2020, the question will change and we should increase the performance.
His proposal focuses on both gas and coal plants with facilities to sterilize the carbon dioxide and, of course, especially on renewable energy.
In this case, he assumes that 18,000 MW will need more, under the Vorraussetzungnatürlich by other "Stützenergien."
Galán, who is of the opinion that the Gesetentwurf for a sustainable economy, which has just been adopted by the government, in line with what has called for his company, wanted to say in no case against this law, how to create incentives for national coal consumption, which is the opposite of all political strategies in the fight against climate change.
In his opinion, "in the long term, we clearly in this direction, despite some" individual "Manahmen, as the chairman of Iberdrola.
Be it as it may, Galán believes that we should already make the decisions on the investment, even if they are in the long term, because it will take some time and a stable remuneration framework must be created to tackle them.
